{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "A new book asserts that an Iranian intelligence officer who is living in the United States under C.I.A. protection oversaw the bombing of the American Embassy in 1983.", "abstract": "Diplomatic Memo; Kai Bird book The Good Spy: The Life and Death of Robert Ames, which spotlights 1983 suicide bombing of American Embassy in Beirut, Lebanon, reveals that Ali Reza Asgari, Iranian intelligence officer who oversaw bombing, defected in 2007 to United States, where he still lives under CIA protection; Asgari was given asylum because he held critical information about Iran's nuclear program; disclosure is timely, given US is in critical phase of nuclear negotiations with Iran.", "section_name": "World", "print_page": "6", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Mark", "role": "reported", "lastname": "LANDLER", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By MARK LANDLER", "contributor": ""}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/05/19/world/middleeast/as-us-looks-to-nuclear-deal-book-faults-handling-of-iranian-defector.html", "lead_paragraph": "A new book asserts that an Iranian intelligence officer who is living in the United States under C.I.A. protection oversaw the bombing of the American Embassy in 1983.", "headline": {"main": "As U.S. Looks to Nuclear Deal, Book Faults Handling of Iranian Defector", "print_headline": "As U.S. Looks to Nuclear Deal, Book Faults Handling of Iranian Defector", "content_kicker": "Listening Post", "kicker": "Listening Post"}, "_id": "53796ef938f0d805525a3426", "word_count": "1048", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2014/05/19/world/POST/POST-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2014/05/19/world/POST/POST-thumbWide.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 395, "url": "images/2014/05/19/world/POST/POST-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/05/19/world/POST/POST-articleLarge.j